{"title_page": "Lijo Jose Pellissery", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian filmmaker}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name                    = Lijo Jose Pellissery\n| image                   = Lijo at IFFI 2018.jpg\n| imagesize               = 160px\n| caption                 = Lijo Jose Pellissery at [[49th International Film Festival of India|IFFI 2018]]\n| birth_date              = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1979|9|18}}\n| birth_place             = [[Cchennai]], [[Kerala]], India\n| other names             = Lijo Jose<br>LJP\n| death_date              =\n| death_place             =\n| restingplace            =\n| restingplacecoordinates =\n| othername               =\n| occupation              = Film director, actor\n| yearsactive             = Since 2010\n| alma mater              = {{ublist|[[Carmel Higher Secondary School, Chalakudy]] | [[Union Christian College, Aluva]] | [[Indian Institute of Plantation Management|IIPM]]}}\n| spouse                  = \n| domesticpartner         =\n| children                = \n| parents                 = [[Jose Pellissery]]<br>Lilly Jose\n| influences              = \n| influenced              =\n| website                 = \n| awards                  = {{ublist|2013&nbsp;[[Asianet Film Award]]|2017&nbsp;Cinema Paradiso Club Award|2017&nbsp;[[Kerala State Film Award]]|2018&nbsp;[[International_Film_Festival_of_Kerala#IFFK_2018|Silver Crow Pheasant IFFK 2018]]}}\n}}\n'''Lijo Jose Pellissery''' is an Indian [[film maker]] and [[actor]] who works in  the [[Malayalam Cinema]]. Known for his unconventional works, he is a recipient of the [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Director|Best Director]] Award at the [[48th Kerala State Film Awards]] for ''[[Ee.Ma.Yau]].'' He is a recipient of Silver Peacock for the best director at the [[49th International Film Festival of India]] and [[50th International Film Festival of India]] for his films ''[[Ee.Ma.Yau]]'' and ''[[Jallikattu (2019 film)|Jallikattu]]'' respectively''.''<ref name=\"\u0d2e\u0d30\u0d23\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4b\u0d33\u0d02 \u0d38\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d38\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d27\u0d02 \u0d08 \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d02; \u0d31\u0d3f\u0d35\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d41\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.manoramaonline.com/movies/movie-reviews/2018/05/04/ee-ma-yau-malayalam-movie-review-lijo-jose-pellissery-chemban-vinod-vinayakan.html |title=\u0d2e\u0d30\u0d23\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4b\u0d33\u0d02 \u0d38\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d38\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d27\u0d02 \u0d08 \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d02; \u0d31\u0d3f\u0d35\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d41 |work=ManoramaOnline |access-date=2018-05-04}}</ref> He also received the Silver Crow Pheasant Award at the [[International Film Festival of Kerala]] 2018.<ref name=\"\u0d32\u0d3f\u0d1c\u0d4b \u0d1c\u0d4b\u0d38\u0d4d \u0d2a\u0d46\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32\u0d3f\u0d36\u0d4d\u0d36\u0d47\u0d30\u0d3f \u0d2e\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a \u0d38\u0d02\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d27\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d15\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d; \u0d21\u0d3e\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d \u0d31\u0d42\u0d02 \u0d2e\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d02\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies-music/specials/iffk-2018/news/iffk-2018-awards-suvarna-chakoram-rajatha-chakoram-lijo-jose-pellissery--1.3391226 |title=\u0d32\u0d3f\u0d1c\u0d4b \u0d1c\u0d4b\u0d38\u0d4d \u0d2a\u0d46\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32\u0d3f\u0d36\u0d4d\u0d36\u0d47\u0d30\u0d3f \u0d2e\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a \u0d38\u0d02\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d27\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d15\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d; \u0d21\u0d3e\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d \u0d31\u0d42\u0d02 \u0d2e\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d02 |date=2018-12-14 |website=Mathrubhumi |access-date=2018-12-14}}</ref>\n\nPellissery  made his debut in 2010 with the crime film ''[[Nayakan (2010 film)|Nayakan]]'' and followed it up with the crime-drama ''[[City of God (2011 film)|City of God]]'' (2011) and the black comedy satire ''[[Amen (2013 film)|Amen]]'' (2013), the last mentioned, a commercial success at the Kerala box office. His fourth film, ''[[Double Barrel (film)|Double Barrel]]'', an experimental film received only mixed reviews. His fifth film was again a crime-gangster film ''[[Angamaly Diaries]]'' (2017), starring almost 90 new actors, which preceded [[Ee.Ma.Yau]], released in 2018. His latest movie is ''[[Jallikkattu]]'', based on a story by [[S. Hareesh]].\n\n==Biography==\n=== Personal life ===\nLijo Jose Pellissery (LJP) was born on September 18, 1979 in [[Chalakudy]] in [[Thrissur district]] of the south Indian state of [[Kerala]] to Lilly and [[Jose Pellissery]], a known film and theater actor and a winner of a state award for best stage actor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mangalam.com/print-edition/sunday-mangalam/46239 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-12-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130404000233/http://www.mangalam.com/print-edition/sunday-mangalam/46239 |archivedate=2013-04-04 }}</ref><ref name=\"The Hindu : Kerala News : Actor Jose Pellissery dead\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehindu.com/2004/12/06/stories/2004120604020500.htm |title=The Hindu : Kerala News : Actor Jose Pellissery dead |date=December 6, 2004 |website=www.thehindu.com |access-date=2018-12-01}}</ref> His schooling was at [[Carmel Higher Secondary School, Chalakudy]] and, after graduating from the [[Union Christian College, Aluva]], he earned a master's degree in business administration from the [[Indian Institute of Plantation Management]], Bangalore.<ref name=\"Lijo Jose Pellissery biography\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.veethi.com/india-people/lijo_jose_pellissery-profile-4496-14.htm |title=Lijo Jose Pellissery biography |date=2018-12-01 |website=veethi.com |access-date=2018-12-01}}</ref>.<ref name=\"Lijo Jose Pellissery to get engaged - Times of India\">{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Lijo-Jose-Pellissery-to-get-engaged/articleshow/50395552.cms |title=Lijo Jose Pellissery to get engaged \u2013 Times of India |work=The Times of India |access-date=2018-05-11}}</ref>\n\n=== Career ===\nBy the time Lijo Pellissery was born, [[Jose Pellissery]] who co-owned a theater group by ''Sarathy Theatres'',<ref name=\"The Hindu : Kerala News : Actor Jose Pellissery dead\"/> was active in Malayalam films and this gave the young Lijo an early grounding in films.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lijo Jose Pellissery IDSFFK|url=http://idsffk.in/2017/06/13/lijo-jose-pellissery/|publisher=IDSFFK|accessdate=1 December 2018|date=1 December 2018}}</ref> His career started as an assistant to Manoj Pillai, an ad filmmaker, and Pellissery soon started making short films of his own. One of his films, ''3'', was one of three films shortlisted for the best film award at the PIX Short Film Festival 2007.<ref name=\"PIX declares winners of its short film fest\">{{Cite web |url=https://businessofcinema.com/bollywood-news/pix-declares-winners-of-its-short-film-fest/21331 |title=PIX declares winners of its short film fest - Businessofcinema.com |date=2007-12-25 |website=Businessofcinema.com |language=en-US |access-date=2018-12-01}}</ref> He debuted as a feature film director in 2010 with ''[[Nayakan (2010 film)|Nayakan]]'', which narrated the story of a [[Kathakali]] artist who joined the underworld to take revenge on those who killed his family. Though the film was critically acclaimed, it failed at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/6450/malayalam/nayakan/2533/review.htm |title=Nayakan Review \u2013 Malayalam Movie Review by VN |publisher=Nowrunning.com |date=2010-03-22 |accessdate=2012-08-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/south-malayalam-movie-review-nayakan/20100322.htm |title=Review: Nayakan is interesting \u2013 Rediff.com Movies |publisher=Rediff.com |date=2010-03-22 |accessdate=2012-08-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/nayakan-review-malayalam-14935888.html |title=Movie Review:Nayakan |publisher=Sify.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Gayathry |first=By |url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/malayalam/reviews/2010/nayakan-movie-review-220310.html |title=Nayakan \u2013 Review &#124; \u2013 Oneindia Entertainment |publisher=Entertainment.oneindia.in |date=2010-03-22 |accessdate=2012-08-22}}</ref> His next venture, ''[[City of God (2011 film)|City of God]]'', one of the early ''New Generation'' films of Malayalam cinema<ref name=\"Malayalam movies: Non-linear narratives are making the box-office ring louder\">{{Cite web |url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/business-of-bollywood/malayalam-movies-non-linear-narratives-are-making-the-box-office-ring-louder/articleshow/8478136.cms |title=Malayalam movies: Non-linear narratives are making the box-office ring louder |date=21 May 2011 |publisher=economictimes |access-date=2011-06-18}}</ref> and a multi-starrer featuring [[Indrajith Sukumaran]], [[Prithviraj Sukumaran]], [[Parvathy Thiruvothu|Parvathy]], [[Swetha Menon]] and [[Rima Kallingal]] used [[hyperlink cinema]] as its narrative structure and was a critical success<ref>{{cite web|title=City Of God Review|url=http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/7811/malayalam/city-of-god/3056/review.htm|work=nowrunning.com \u2013  \"don't miss the show!\"|publisher=INFOCON LLC|accessdate=17 June 2012|author=Veeyen|date=24 April 2011}}</ref> but, again failed miserably at the box office; it was pulled from cinemas just days after its release.<ref name=\"Review: City Of God is worth a watch\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-city-of-god/20110425.htm |title=Review: City Of God is worth a watch |date=April 25, 2011 |website=Rediff |access-date=2018-12-02}}</ref>\n\nIt took another two years before he came up with his third movie, ''[[Amen (2013 film)|Amen]]'', in 2013, which had [[Indrajith Sukumaran]], [[Fahad Fasil]], [[Swathi Reddy]] and [[Kalabhavan Mani]] in the lead roles and the movie succeeded at the box office while drawing good critical response.<ref name=\"Fahadh Faasil\u2019s Amen turns four!\">{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/fahadh-faasils-amen-turns-four/articleshow/57771454.cms |title=Fahadh Faasil\u2019s Amen turns four! \u2013 Times of India |date=March 22, 2017 |website=The Times of India |access-date=2018-12-01}}</ref><ref name=\"Review: Amen is brilliant\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.rediff.com/movies/review/south-review-amen-is-brilliant/20130325.htm |title=Review: Amen is brilliant |date=December 1, 2018 |website=Rediff |access-date=December 1, 2018}}</ref> After a gap of almost two years, Pellissery released his fourth film, ''[[Double Barrel (film)|Double Barrel]]'', a comic thriller, with [[Prithviraj Sukumaran]], [[Indrajith Sukumaran]],  [[Arya (actor)|Arya]], [[Sunny Wayne]] and [[Asif Ali (actor)|Asif Ali]] in the lead roles. However, the film did not succeed critically or commercially.<ref name=\"Double Barrel Movie Review\">{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movie-reviews/Double-Barrel/movie-review/48731110.cms |title=Double Barrel Movie Review {2.5/5}: Critic Review of Double Barrel by Times of India |date=April 6, 2016 |website=Times of India |access-date=2018-12-02}}</ref> The next project, ''[[Angamaly Diaries]]'', a black comedy cloaked in a gangster plot that revolves around the locale of [[Angamaly]], was scripted by popular actor, [[Chemban Vinod Jose]].<ref name=\"Angamaly Diaries review: Here's what celebs have to say about Lijo Jose Pellissery's movie\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/angamaly-diaries-review-heres-what-celebs-have-say-about-lijo-jose-pellisserys-movie-after-717899 |title=Angamaly Diaries review: Here's what celebs have to say about Lijo Jose Pellissery's movie |last=James |first=Anu |date=2018-12-02 |website=International Business Times, India Edition |access-date=2018-12-02}}</ref> The film, made on a small budget of {{INR|30}} million,<ref name=\"Small is beautiful: Malayalam cinema's low budget films are scoring big at the box office\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/small-beautiful-malayalam-cinemas-low-budget-films-are-scoring-big-box-office-68054 |title=Small is beautiful: Malayalam cinema's low budget films are scoring big at the box office |date=2017-09-07 |website=The News Minute |access-date=2018-12-02}}</ref> was received well at the box office and drew critical acclaim; [[Anurag Kashyap]] opined that ''Angamaly Diaries'' was his film of the year.<ref name=\"And...the best film of the year is Angamaly Diaries, says Anurag Kashyap! - Times of India\">{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/and-the-best-film-of-the-year-is-angamaly-diaries-says-anurag-kashyap/articleshow/57750726.cms |title=And...the best film of the year is Angamaly Diaries, says Anurag Kashyap! \u2013 Times of India |work=The Times of India |access-date=2018-05-11}}</ref><ref name=\"Angamaly Diaries: Here Is What Anurag Kashyap Has  To Say About The Movie!\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.filmibeat.com/malayalam/news/2017/angamaly-diaries-here-is-what-anurag-kashyap-has-got-to-say-about-the-movie-256900.html |title=Angamaly Diaries: Here Is What Anurag Kashyap Has  To Say About The Movie! |date=2018-12-02 |website=filmibeat.com |language=en |access-date=2018-12-02}}</ref> ''[[Ee.Ma.Yau]]'', his next film based on a satire written by [[P. F. Mathews]]<ref name=\"Angamaly Storyteller, Lijo Jose Pellissery Has taken Contemporary Malayalam Cinema By Storm\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.mansworldindia.com/cinema/angamaly-storyteller-lijo-jose-pellissery-taken-contemporary-malayalam-cinema-storm/ |title=Angamaly Storyteller, Lijo Jose Pellissery Has taken Contemporary Malayalam Cinema By Storm |date=2018-04-17 |website=Man's World India |language=en-GB |access-date=2018-12-02}}</ref> and with his regular composer, [[Prashant Pillai]], scoring the music,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2018/jul/23/french-viplavam-releasing-in-sept-7096.html|title=French Viplavam to be released in September|work=Cinema Express|date=23 July 2018|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref> was premiered on November 30, 2017<ref name=\"\u2018Ee.Ma.Yau\u2019 preview: A death and the events that follow\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/lijo-jose-pellissery-about-his-new-movie-eemayau/article21210194.ece |title=\u2018Ee.Ma.Yau\u2019 preview: A death and the events that follow |last=M |first=Athira |date=2017-11-30 |website=The Hindu |language=en-IN |access-date=2018-12-02}}</ref> but the release was delayed due to undisclosed reasons.<ref name=\"Release of Lijo Jose\u2019s 'Ee Ma Yau' postponed to 2018\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/release-lijo-jose-s-ee-ma-yau-postponed-2018-73483 |title=Release of Lijo Jose\u2019s 'Ee Ma Yau' postponed to 2018 |date=2017-12-20 |website=The News Minute |access-date=2018-12-02}}</ref> Before it was released on May 4, 2018, the film received the [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Director]] at the [[48th Kerala State Film Awards]].<ref name=\"\u0d2e\u0d30\u0d23\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4b\u0d33\u0d02 \u0d38\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d38\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d27\u0d02 \u0d08 \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d02; \u0d31\u0d3f\u0d35\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d41\" /> The film also won him the ''Silver Peacock'' Award for the best director at the 49th [[International Film Festival of India]] (IFFI), 2018, which was held in [[Goa]] in November 2018<ref name=\"IFFI: Chemban Vinod and Lijo Jose Pellissery bag big wins at the film fest - Times of India\">{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/66850554.cms |title=IFFI: Chemban Vinod and Lijo Jose Pellissery bag big wins at the film fest \u2013 Times of India |date=2018-12-01 |website=The Times of India |access-date=2018-12-01}}</ref> ([[Chemban Vinod Jose]], the protagonist of the film, also received the ''Silver Peacock'' Award for the best actor.<ref name=\"The unpredictable mind behind 'Ee.Ma Yau': Lijo Jose Pellissery interview\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/unpredictable-mind-behind-eema-yau-lijo-jose-pellissery-interview-92576 |title=The unpredictable mind behind 'Ee.Ma Yau': Lijo Jose Pellissery interview |date=2018-12-01 |website=The News Minute |access-date=2018-12-02}}</ref>) followed by the Sinema Zetu International Film Festival Award for Best Direction.<ref name=\"SZIFF - International Film Festival Tanzania\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.sziff.co.tz/all_films_2019 |title=SZIFF \u2013 International Film Festival Tanzania |date=2019-03-05 |website=sziff.co.tz |access-date=2019-03-05}}\n</ref>\n\n=== Influences and style of film making ===\nA fan of film makers such as [[K. G. George]], [[Padmarajan]], [[Akira Kurosawa]], [[Quentin Tarantino]] and [[Francis Ford Coppola]],<ref>[I Personally \u2013 Lijo Jose Pellissery \u2013 Part 03 Kappa TV (YouTube Video) YouTube Channel]</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/gateway/lijojose.html |title=Welcome to Gateway |date=2018-12-02 |publisher=Rediff.com |access-date=2012-08-22}}</ref> Pellissery often uses non-linear style of narrative.<ref name=\"Malayalam movies: Non-linear narratives are making the box-office ring louder\" /> His early films had established actors in the lead roles but [[Angamaly Diaries]] marked a change where almost the entire cast were newcomers with 86 new actors making their debut, and subsequently accomplishing a triumph in the form of a 11-minute [[long take|uninterrupted long take]] in the climax.<ref name=\"Angamaly Diaries: Meet the director whose Malayalam film is probably the best this year\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/angamaly-diaries-meet-the-director-whose-malayalam-film-is-probably-the-best-this-year/story-BBFwlYgca6sVnDY1g5LtoM.html |title=Angamaly Diaries: Meet the director whose Malayalam film is probably the best this year |date=2017-04-30 |website=hindustantimes.com |language=en |access-date=2018-12-02}}</ref> <ref name=\"EE. Ma. Yau: Five reasons to watch Lijo Jose Pellissery\">{{Cite web |url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/ee-ma-yau-review-five-reasons-to-watch-lijo-jose-pellissery-movie-review/amp_articleshow/61867725.cms |title=EE. Ma. Yau: Five reasons to watch Lijo Jose Pellissery \u2013 Times of India |date=2018-12-02 |website=The Times of India |language=en |access-date=2018-12-02}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"width:75%\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:27%\" | Award\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:17%\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:23%\" | Film\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2013|| [[Asianet Film Award]]|| Best Director|| align=\"center\" | ''[[Amen (2013 film)|Amen]]''\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2013|| Atlas Film Critics Award|| Best popular movie|| align=\"center\" | ''[[Amen (2013 film)|Amen]]''\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2014|| Royal Reel Award-Canada Film Festival || Best film || align=\"center\" | ''[[Amen (2013 film)|Amen]]''\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2017 || Cinema Paradiso Club Award || Best Director || align=\"center\" | ''[[Angamaly Diaries]]''\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2017 || [[Kerala State Film Award]] || Best Director || align=\"center\" | ''[[Ee.Ma.Yau]]''\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2018 || [[49th International Film Festival of India|Silver Peacock IFFI 2018]] || Best Director || align=\"center\" | ''[[Ee.Ma.Yau]]''\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2018 || [[International Film Festival of Kerala|Golden Crow Pheasant IFFK 2018]] || Best Director || align=\"center\" | ''[[Ee.Ma.Yau]]''\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2019 || Sinema Zetu International Film Festival Award SZIFF 2019 || Best Director || align=\"center\" | ''[[Ee.Ma.Yau]]