y 28, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190226173305/https://www.chicagotribune.com/sns-bc-esp-tel-umbrella-academy-david-castaeda-20190223-story.html |archive-date=February 26, 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref> but raised in [[Sinaloa]], [[Mexico]].<ref name=\"golden globes\"/> He returned to the United States where he attended high school when he was 14.<ref name=\"chicago tribune\" /> Casta\u00f1eda initially studied [[civil engineering]] in college with the intention of taking over the family business after he finished his studies.<ref name=status /> However, he became interested in film direction, and switched to major in film production and international business at [[California State University, Fullerton]], where he had attended since 2007.<ref name=\"golden globes\">{{cite web |url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/articles/david-castaneda-el-morro-de-burgermania-anda-de-actor-en-hollywood |title=David Casta\u00f1eda: 'El morro de Burgerman\u00eda anda de actor en Hollywood' |first= Gabriel |last=Lerman |date=February 15, 2019 |publisher=[[Golden Globes]]|accessdate=February 28, 2019|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=titan>{{cite web |url=https://dailytitan.com/2013/11/student-balances-acting-with-responsibilities-on-switched-at-birth-tv-series/ |title=Student balances acting with responsibilities on ''Switched at Birth'' TV series |first=Sonam |last= Mirpuri |date=November 5, 2013 |work=Daily Titan|accessdate=February 28, 2019}}</ref> Casta\u00f1eda then moved into acting and started auditioning for roles. He studied part-time while pursuing an acting career, eventually graduating in 2015.<ref name=titan /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/2xAZXRm4VY/ |title=Assemble |author=castanedawong|website=[[Instagram]] |date=May 17, 2015 |accessdate=February 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nCastaneda has been involved in acting since he was 17,<ref name=status>{{cite web |url=http://statusmagonline.com/features/davidcastaneda-interview-february2019/ |title=David Casta\u00f1eda Steers His Plans To An Action-Packed Acting Career |first=Nikki |last=Yap|date=February 2019 |work=Status |via=statusmagonline.com |accessdate=February 28, 2019}}</ref> but only started taking acting more seriously after he volunteered for a role when a director asked for actors to participate in his film during a seminar while at university.<ref name=titan /> He played various minor roles in a number of productions, such as ''[[End of Watch]]'', and also acted as a main character in a short film ''Maddoggin{{'}}'', which won the audience award at the NBC Universal Short Cut Film Festival.<ref name=titan /> In 2013, he landed a role playing Jorge on [[ABC Family]]'s TV series ''[[Switched at Birth (TV series)|Switched at Birth]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/melissa-joey-switched-at-birth-650299 |title=''Melissa & Joey'', ''Switched at Birth'' Add Guest Stars |date=October 23, 2013 |first= Philiana |last=Ng |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=February 28, 2019 }}</ref> In late 2016, he was cast in the role of Hector in the film ''[[Sicario: Day of the Soldado]]'' released in 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://variety.com/2016/film/news/david-castaneda-sicario-sequel-soldado-1201943575/ |title= David Castaneda Joins ''Sicario'' Sequel ''Soldado''|first= Justin |last= Kroll |work=Variety |date=December 15, 2016|accessdate=February 28, 2019}}</ref>  He also has a major role in an independent film ''[[El Chicano (film)|El Chicano]]'', a supporting role in [[Jean-Claude Van Damme]]'s ''We Die Young'' as well as minor roles in films such as the [[Billy Crystal]]'s film ''[[Standing Up, Falling Down]]''.<ref name=status />\n\nIn 2017, he was cast in his most prominent role yet playing Diego Hargreeves / Number 2 in ''[[The Umbrella Academy (TV series)|The Umbrella Academy]]'', which was released on [[Netflix]] in February 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/umbrella-academy