olloman AFB Photo Page]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070202073531/http://www.holloman.af.mil/library/ Holloman AFB Library]\n* [http://www.hollomanunderground.com/index.jsp Holloman Underground] \u2013 unofficial guide to local area\n* {{FAA-diagram|00007}}\n{{US-airport-mil|HMN}}\n\n{{US Air Force navbox}}\n{{USAF Air Combat Command}}\n{{Tactical Air Command}}\n{{USAAF 2d Air Force World War II}}\n{{NMMilitary}}\n{{Otero County, New Mexico}}\n{{New Mexico during World War II}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Installations of the United States Air Force in New Mexico]]\n[[Category:Airports in New Mexico]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Otero County, New Mexico]]\n[[Category:Alamogordo, New Mexico]]\n[[Category:Census-designated places in Otero County, New Mexico]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Otero County, New Mexico]]\n[[Category:Tularosa Basin]]\n[[Category:Military installations established in 1948]]\n[[Category:Initial United States Air Force installations]]\n[[Category:History of Otero County, New Mexico]]\n[[Category:Post-World War II aircraft storage facilities]]\n[[Category:Bases of the German Air Force]]\n[[Category:Census-designated places in New Mexico]]\n[[Category:Overseas or abroad military installations]]\n[[Category:World War II airfields in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{redirect|Holloman|the surname|Holloman (surname)}}\n{{more citations needed|date=February 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox military installation\n| name = Holloman Air Force Base\n| ensign = \n| ensign_size =\n| native_name = \n| partof = <!-- for elements within a larger site -->\n| location = \n| nearest_town = [[Alamogordo, New Mexico|Alamogordo]], [[New Mexico]]\n| country = [[United States of America]]\n| image = File:311th Fighter Squadron General Dynamics F-16D Block 42E Fighting Falcon 89-2157.jpg\n| alt = A [[General Dynamics F-16 Fighting Falcon|F-16 Fighting Falcon]] of the [[54th Fighter Group]] at Holloman Air Force B