ALIGN=\"center\"\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 1995-96\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | [[FPS (ice hockey)|FPS]]\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | [[Mestis|1. Divisioona]]\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 41\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 11\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 36\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 47\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 2\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 5\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 1\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 5\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 6\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"3\" | SM-liiga Totals\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 99\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 26\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 33\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 59\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 16\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 12\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 2\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 2\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 4\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"3\" | 1. Divisioona Totals\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 580\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 295\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 522\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 817\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 178\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 5\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 1\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 5\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 6\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n|}\n\n==References==\n*{{hockeydb|64714}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Helkearo, Mika}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Forssa]]\n[[Category:FoPS players]]\n[[Category:Jokerit players]]\n[[Category:HIFK (ice hockey) players]]\n[[Category:HPK players]]\n[[Category:Finnish ice hockey forwards]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox ice hockey player\n| image= \n| played_for = '''[[SM-liiga]]''' <br> [[HIFK (ice hockey)|HIFK]] <br> [[HPK]] <br> [[Jokerit]] <br> '''[[Mestis|1. Divisioona]]''' <br> [[FPS (ice hockey)|FPS]]\n| position = [[Forward (ice hockey)|Forward]]\n| shoots = Left\n| height_ft = 5\n| height_in = 10\n| weight_lb = 180\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1960|10|04}}\n| birth_place = [[Forssa]], [[Finland|FIN]]\n| draft = \n| draft_year = \n| draft_team = \n| career_start = 1977\n| career_end = 1996\n}}\n\n'''Mika Helkearo''' (born October 4, 1960) is a retired professional [[ice hockey]] player. He was born in [[Forssa]], [[Finland]].\n\nHelkearo is best known from his tenure in Finnish [[Mestis|First Division]] team [[FPS (ice hockey)|FPS]] where he posted 817 points in 580 First Division games.\n\nHelkearo's records are being considered virtually unbreakable and he holds the records for most Mestis/1. Divisioona games, most Mestis/1. Divisioona assists and most Mestis/1. Divisioona points as [[H\u00e5kan Hjerpe]], the only one who is even close to Helkearo's numbers has the record for most Mestis/1. Divisioona goals (317 goals).\n\nCause of this, Helkearo is called \"Divarin Gretzky\", Gretzky of the First Division, as a nod to famous [[National Hockey League]] player [[Wayne Gretzky]], who has big numbers on his all-time stats for NHL.\n\nHelkearo also played in the top league of Finland, the [[SM-liiga]] where he played two seasons for [[HIFK (ice hockey)|HIFK]], 1981\u201382 and 1982\u201383, one season for [[HPK]], 1983\u201384 and a single game for [[Jokerit]] in 1993-94 season.\n\nHelkearo retired in 1996. Helkearo was 36 years of age when he retired.\n\nHelkearo's Jersey number 15 has been retired by FPS.\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| BORDER=\"0\" CELLPADDING=\"3\" CELLSPACING=\"0\" ID=\"Table3\"\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! ALIGN=\"center\" colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | &nbsp;\n! ALIGN=\"center\" rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | &nbsp;\n! ALIGN=\"center\" colspan=\"5\" | Regular&nbsp;Season\n! ALIGN=\"center\" rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | &nbsp;\n! ALIGN=\"center\" colspan=\"5\" | Playoffs\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | Season\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | Team\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | League\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | GP\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | G\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | A\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | Pts\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | PIM\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | GP\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | G\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | A\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | Pts\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | PIM\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 1977-78\n| ALIGN=\"center\"